Create a system architecture diagram showing:
- Motive software box (left)
- UDP connection (1511) labeled "NatNet Protocol"
- NatNet Client box (middle)
- Async callback arrow to DataHandler
- MotiveStreamer ROS2 Node box
- ROS2 publishers to PoseStamped and MotiveRigidBodyList topics
- Downstream control box (MoveIt2, Planning) subscribing to topics
- DataDescriptions metadata flow for ID↔Name mapping

Style: Clean boxes and arrows, professional color scheme (blues/grays)
Tools: draw.io, Lucidchart, or Excalidraw
Resolution: 1400px width, PNG format
